{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"It was an incredible surprise to me"},{"time":4000,"text":"to find out that there was actually an organization that cared about both parts of my life."},{"time":10000,"text":"Because, basically,"},{"time":11000,"text":"I work as a theoretical physicist."},{"time":13000,"text":"I develop and test models of the Big Bang,"},{"time":16000,"text":"using observational data."},{"time":19000,"text":"And I've been moonlighting for the last five years"},{"time":22000,"text":"helping with a project in Africa."},{"time":25000,"text":"And, I get a lot of flak for this at Cambridge."},{"time":29000,"text":"People wonder, you know, \"How do you have time to do this?\" And so on."},{"time":33000,"text":"And so it was simply astonishing to me"},{"time":36000,"text":"to find an organization that actually appreciated both those sides."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"So I thought I'd start off by just telling you a little bit about myself"},{"time":43000,"text":"and why I lead this schizophrenic life."},{"time":47000,"text":"Well, I was born in South Africa and my parents were imprisoned"},{"time":52000,"text":"for resisting the racist regime."},{"time":54000,"text":"When they were released, we left and we went as refugees to Kenya and Tanzania."},{"time":61000,"text":"Both were very young countries then,"},{"time":63000,"text":"and full of hope for the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"We had an amazing childhood. We didn't have any money,"},{"time":68000,"text":"but we were outdoors most of the time."},{"time":71000,"text":"We had fantastic friends and we saw the wonders of the world,"},{"time":76000,"text":"like Kilimanjaro, Serengeti and the Olduvai Gorge."},{"time":82000,"text":"Well, then we moved to London for high school."},{"time":84000,"text":"And after that -- there's nothing much to say about that."},{"time":89000,"text":"It was rather dull. But I came back to Africa"},{"time":93000,"text":"at the age of 17, as a volunteer teacher"},{"time":97000,"text":"to Lesotho, which is a tiny country,"},{"time":100000,"text":"surrounded at that time by apartheid South Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105000,"text":"Well, 80 percent of the men in Lesotho"},{"time":108000,"text":"worked in the mines over the border,"},{"time":112000,"text":"in brutal conditions."},{"time":115000,"text":"Nevertheless, I -- as I'm sure -- as a rather irritating young, white man"},{"time":121000,"text":"coming into their village, I was welcomed with incredible hospitality and warmth."},{"time":127000,"text":"But the kids were the best part."},{"time":129000,"text":"The kids were amazing: extremely eager and often very bright."},{"time":134000,"text":"And I'm just going to tell you one story,"},{"time":136000,"text":"which got through to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"I used to try to take the kids outside as often as possible,"},{"time":141000,"text":"to try to connect the academic stuff with the real world."},{"time":146000,"text":"And they weren't used to that."},{"time":149000,"text":"But I took them outside one day and I said,"},{"time":151000,"text":"\"I want you to estimate the height of the building.\""},{"time":154000,"text":"And I expected them to put a ruler next to the wall,"},{"time":157000,"text":"size it up with a finger, and make an estimate of the height."},{"time":162000,"text":"But there was one little boy, very small for his age."},{"time":166000,"text":"He was the son of one of the poorest families in the village."},{"time":169000,"text":"And he wasn't doing that. He was scribbling with chalk on the pavement."},{"time":174000,"text":"And so, I said -- I was annoyed -- I said, \"What are you doing?"},{"time":177000,"text":"I want you to estimate the height of the building.\""},{"time":179000,"text":"He said, \"OK. I measured the height of a brick."},{"time":182000,"text":"I counted the number of bricks and now I'm multiplying.\""},{"time":187000,"text":"Well -- (Laughter) -- I hadn't thought of that one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"And many experiences like this happened to me."},{"time":196000,"text":"Another one is that I met a miner. He was home on his three-month leave from the mines."},{"time":204000,"text":"Sitting next to him one day, he said, \"There's only one thing that I really loved at school."},{"time":210000,"text":"And you know what it was? Shakespeare.\" And he recited some to me."},{"time":217000,"text":"And these and many similar experiences convinced me"},{"time":221000,"text":"that there are just tons of bright kids in Africa"},{"time":225000,"text":"-- inventive kids, intellectual kids --"},{"time":229000,"text":"and starved of opportunity."},{"time":230000,"text":"And if Africa is going to get fixed, it's by them, not by us."},{"time":236000,"text":"Well, after -- (Applause) -- that's the truth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242000,"text":"Well, after Lesotho, I traveled across Africa"},{"time":245000,"text":"before returning to England"},{"time":248000,"text":"-- so gray and depressing, in comparison."},{"time":251000,"text":"And I went to Cambridge. And there, I fell for theoretical physics."},{"time":258000,"text":"Well, I'm not going to explain this equation,"},{"time":260000,"text":"but theoretical physics is really an amazing subject."},{"time":264000,"text":"We can write down all the laws of physics we know in one line."},{"time":270000,"text":"And, admittedly, it's in a very shorthand notation."},{"time":275000,"text":"And it contains 18 free parameters,"},{"time":279000,"text":"OK, which we have to fit to the data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282000,"text":"So it's not the final story,"},{"time":284000,"text":"but it's an incredibly powerful summary of everything we know"},{"time":289000,"text":"about nature at the most basic level."},{"time":293000,"text":"And apart from a few very important loose ends, which you've heard about here --"},{"time":297000,"text":"like dark energy and dark matter --"},{"time":300000,"text":"this equation describes,"},{"time":302000,"text":"seems to describe everything about the universe and what's in it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307000,"text":"But there's one big puzzle remaining,"},{"time":309000,"text":"and this was most succinctly put to me by my primary school math teacher in"},{"time":314000,"text":"Tanzania, who's a wonderful Scottish lady"},{"time":317000,"text":"who I still stay in touch with."},{"time":320000,"text":"And she's now in her 80s."},{"time":322000,"text":"And when I try to explain my work to her, she waved away all the details, and she said,"},{"time":327000,"text":"\"Neil, there's only one question that really matters."},{"time":332000,"text":"What banged?\" (Laughter)"},{"time":336000,"text":"\"Everyone talks about the Big Bang. What banged?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"And she's right. It's a question we've all been avoiding."},{"time":346000,"text":"The standard explanation is that the universe somehow sprang into existence,"},{"time":351000,"text":"full of a strange kind of energy"},{"time":353000,"text":"-- inflationary energy -- which blew it up."},{"time":358000,"text":"But the puzzle of why the universe emerged in that peculiar state"},{"time":362000,"text":"is completely unsolved."},{"time":366000,"text":"Now, I worked on that theory for a while, with Stephen Hawking and others."},{"time":370000,"text":"But then I began to explore another alternative."},{"time":373000,"text":"The alternative is that the Big Bang wasn't the beginning."},{"time":376000,"text":"Perhaps the universe existed before the bang,"},{"time":379000,"text":"and the bang was just a violent event in a pre-existing universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"Well, this possibility is actually suggested"},{"time":387000,"text":"by the latest theories, the unified theories,"},{"time":390000,"text":"which try to explain all those 18 free parameters"},{"time":393000,"text":"in a single framework, which will hopefully predict all of them."},{"time":400000,"text":"And I'll just share a cartoon of this idea here."},{"time":403000,"text":"It's all I can convey. According to these theories,"},{"time":406000,"text":"there are extra dimensions of space, not just the three we're familiar with,"},{"time":409000,"text":"but at every point in the room there are more dimensions."},{"time":413000,"text":"And in particular, there's one rather strange one,"},{"time":415000,"text":"in the most elegant unified theories we have."},{"time":418000,"text":"The strange one looks likes this:"},{"time":420000,"text":"that we live in a three-dimensional world."},{"time":423000,"text":"We live in one of these worlds, and I can only show it as a sheet,"},{"time":427000,"text":"but it's really three-dimensional."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430000,"text":"And a tiny distance away, there's another sheet,"},{"time":434000,"text":"also three-dimensional, and they're separated by a gap."},{"time":436000,"text":"The gap is very tiny, and I've blown it up so you can see it."},{"time":439000,"text":"But it's really a tiny fraction of the size of an atomic nucleus."},{"time":444000,"text":"I won't go into the details of why we think the universe is like this,"},{"time":447000,"text":"but it comes out of the math and trying to explain the physics that we know."},{"time":451000,"text":"Well, I got interested in this because it seemed to me that it was an obvious question."},{"time":455000,"text":"Which is, what happens if these two, three-dimensional worlds"},{"time":458000,"text":"should actually collide?"},{"time":462000,"text":"And if they collide, it would look a lot like the Big Bang."},{"time":465000,"text":"But it's slightly different than in the conventional picture."},{"time":468000,"text":"The conventional picture of the Big Bang is a point."},{"time":470000,"text":"Everything comes out of a point;"},{"time":472000,"text":"you have infinite density. And all the equations break down."},{"time":476000,"text":"No hope of describing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"In this picture, you'll notice,"},{"time":480000,"text":"the bang is extended. It's not a point."},{"time":482000,"text":"The density of matter is finite, and we have a chance"},{"time":485000,"text":"of a consistent set of equations that can describe the whole process."},{"time":490000,"text":"So, to cut a long story short, we've explored this alternative."},{"time":493000,"text":"We've shown that it can fit"},{"time":495000,"text":"all of the data that we have about the formation of galaxies,"},{"time":499000,"text":"the fluctuations in the microwave background."},{"time":502000,"text":"Furthermore, there's an experimental way"},{"time":504000,"text":"to tell this theory, apart from the inflationary explanation that I told you before."},{"time":511000,"text":"It involves gravitational waves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"And in this scenario, not only was the Big Bang not the beginning,"},{"time":517000,"text":"as you can see from the picture,"},{"time":520000,"text":"it can happen over and over again."},{"time":522000,"text":"It may be that we live in an endless universe,"},{"time":525000,"text":"both in space and in time."},{"time":529000,"text":"And there've been bangs in the past, and there will be bangs in the future."},{"time":532000,"text":"And maybe we live in an endless universe."},{"time":536000,"text":"Well, making and testing models of the universe"},{"time":541000,"text":"is, for me, the best way I have of enjoying and appreciating the universe."},{"time":548000,"text":"We need to make the best mathematical models we can,"},{"time":550000,"text":"the most consistent ones."},{"time":552000,"text":"And then we scrutinize them, logically and with data."},{"time":556000,"text":"And we try to convince ourselves --"},{"time":559000,"text":"we really try to convince ourselves they're wrong."},{"time":561000,"text":"That's progress: when we prove things wrong."},{"time":564000,"text":"And gradually, we hopefully move closer and closer to understanding the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570000,"text":"As I pursued my career, something was always gnawing away inside me."},{"time":575000,"text":"What about Africa?"},{"time":578000,"text":"What about those kids I'd left behind?"},{"time":583000,"text":"Instead of developing, as we'd all hoped in the '60s,"},{"time":586000,"text":"things had gotten worse."},{"time":588000,"text":"Africa was gripped by poverty, disease and war."},{"time":592000,"text":"This is very graphically shown by the Worldmapper website and project."},{"time":598000,"text":"And so the idea is to represent each country"},{"time":601000,"text":"on a map, but scale the area according to some quantity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607000,"text":"So here's just the standard area map of the world."},{"time":609000,"text":"By the way, Africa is very large."},{"time":611000,"text":"And the next map now shows Africa's GDP in 1960,"},{"time":616000,"text":"around the time of independence for many African states."},{"time":621000,"text":"Now, this is 1990, and then 2002. And here's a projection for 2015."},{"time":632000,"text":"Big changes are happening in the world,"},{"time":633000,"text":"but they're not helping Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"What about Africa's population? The population isn't out of proportion to its area,"},{"time":640000,"text":"but Africa leads the world in deaths from often preventable causes:"},{"time":645000,"text":"malnutrition, simple infections and birth complications."},{"time":652000,"text":"Then there's HIV/AIDS. And then there are deaths from war."},{"time":657000,"text":"OK, currently there are 45,000 people a month dying in the Congo,"},{"time":662000,"text":"as a consequence of the war"},{"time":664000,"text":"there over coltan and diamonds and other things."},{"time":668000,"text":"It's still going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672000,"text":"What about Africa's capacity to do something about these problems?"},{"time":675000,"text":"Well, here's the number of physicians in Africa."},{"time":680000,"text":"Here's the number of people in higher education."},{"time":685000,"text":"And here -- most shocking to me --"},{"time":687000,"text":"the number of scientific research papers coming out of Africa."},{"time":691000,"text":"It just doesn't exist scientifically."},{"time":696000,"text":"And this was very eloquently argued at TED Africa:"},{"time":699000,"text":"that all of the aid that's been given"},{"time":701000,"text":"has completely failed to put Africa onto its own two feet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709000,"text":"Well, the transition to democracy in South Africa in 1994"},{"time":712000,"text":"was literally a dream come true for many of us."},{"time":716000,"text":"My parents were both elected to the first parliament,"},{"time":719000,"text":"alongside Nelson and Winnie Mandela. They were the only other couple."},{"time":724000,"text":"And in 2001, I took a research leave to visit them."},{"time":728000,"text":"And while I was busy working -- I was working on these colliding worlds, in the day."},{"time":735000,"text":"But I learned that there was a desperate shortage of skills,"},{"time":738000,"text":"especially mathematical skills, in industry, in government, in education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"The ability to make and test models has become essential,"},{"time":750000,"text":"not only to every single area of science today,"},{"time":753000,"text":"but also to modern society itself."},{"time":757000,"text":"And if you don't have math, you're not going to enter the modern age."},{"time":763000,"text":"So I had an idea. And the idea was very simple."},{"time":766000,"text":"The idea was to set up an African Institute for Mathematical Sciences, or AIMS."},{"time":772000,"text":"And let's recruit students from the whole of Africa,"},{"time":776000,"text":"bring them together with lecturers from all over the world,"},{"time":780000,"text":"and we'll try to give them a fantastic education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785000,"text":"Well, as a Cambridge professor, I had many contacts."},{"time":788000,"text":"And to my astonishment, they backed me 100 percent."},{"time":791000,"text":"They said, \"Go and do it,"},{"time":793000,"text":"and we'll come and lecture.\""},{"time":797000,"text":"And I knew it would be amazing fun to bring brilliant students"},{"time":801000,"text":"from these countries -- where they don't have any opportunities -- together"},{"time":805000,"text":"with the best lecturers in the world --"},{"time":807000,"text":"who I knew would come, because of the interest in Africa --"},{"time":810000,"text":"and put them together and just let the sparks fly."},{"time":817000,"text":"So we bought a derelict hotel near Cape Town."},{"time":821000,"text":"It's an 80-room Art Deco hotel from the 1920s."},{"time":824000,"text":"The area was kind of seedy, so we got an 80-room hotel for 100,000 dollars."},{"time":830000,"text":"It's a beautiful building. We decided we would refurbish it"},{"time":834000,"text":"and then put out the word:"},{"time":836000,"text":"we're going to start the best math institute in Africa"},{"time":840000,"text":"in this hotel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"Well, the new South Africa is a very exciting country."},{"time":844000,"text":"And those of you who haven't been there, you should go."},{"time":847000,"text":"It's very, very interesting what's happening."},{"time":850000,"text":"And we recruited wonderful staff,"},{"time":853000,"text":"highly motivated staff."},{"time":855000,"text":"The other thing that's happened, which was good for us, is the Internet."},{"time":859000,"text":"Even though the Internet is very expensive all over Africa,"},{"time":862000,"text":"there are Internet cafes everywhere."},{"time":864000,"text":"And bright young Africans are desperate to join the global community,"},{"time":869000,"text":"to be successful -- and they're very ambitious."},{"time":872000,"text":"They want to be the next Einstein."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878000,"text":"And so when word came out that AIMS was opening,"},{"time":881000,"text":"it spread very quickly via e-mail and our website."},{"time":885000,"text":"And we got lots of applicants."},{"time":887000,"text":"Well, we designed AIMS as a 24-hour learning environment,"},{"time":890000,"text":"and it was fantastic to start a university from the beginning."},{"time":894000,"text":"You have to rethink, what is the university for?"},{"time":898000,"text":"And that's really exciting."},{"time":900000,"text":"So we designed it to have interactive teaching."},{"time":903000,"text":"No droning on at the chalkboard."},{"time":907000,"text":"We emphasize problem-solving, working in groups,"},{"time":911000,"text":"every student discovering and maximizing their own potential"},{"time":915000,"text":"and not chasing grades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":918000,"text":"Everyone lives together in this hotel -- lecturers and students --"},{"time":920000,"text":"and it's not surprising at all to find an impromptu tutorial at 1 a.m."},{"time":926000,"text":"The students don't usually leave the computer lab till 2 or 3 a.m."},{"time":930000,"text":"And then they're up again at eight in the morning."},{"time":932000,"text":"Lectures, problem-solving and so on. It's an extraordinary place."},{"time":939000,"text":"We especially emphasize areas of great relevance to Africa's development,"},{"time":944000,"text":"because, in those areas, scientists working in Africa will have a competitive advantage."},{"time":950000,"text":"They'll publish, be invited to conferences."},{"time":952000,"text":"They'll do well. They'll have successful careers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958000,"text":"And AIMS has done extremely well."},{"time":960000,"text":"Here is a list of last year's graduates, graduated in June,"},{"time":964000,"text":"and what they're currently doing -- 48 of them."},{"time":967000,"text":"And where they are is indicated over here."},{"time":971000,"text":"And where they've gone. So these are all postgraduate students."},{"time":975000,"text":"And they've all gone on to master's and Ph.D. degrees in excellent places."},{"time":982000,"text":"Five students can be educated at AIMS"},{"time":984000,"text":"for the cost of educating one in the U.S. or Europe."},{"time":988000,"text":"But more important, the pan-African student body"},{"time":991000,"text":"is a continual source of strength, pride and commitment to Africa."},{"time":997000,"text":"We illustrate AIMS' progress by coloring in the countries of Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002000,"text":"So here you can see behind this list."},{"time":1004000,"text":"When a county is colored yellow, we've received an application;"},{"time":1008000,"text":"orange, we've accepted an application; and green,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"a student has graduated."},{"time":1015000,"text":"So here is where we were after the first graduation in 2004."},{"time":1019000,"text":"And we set ourselves a goal of turning the continent green."},{"time":1023000,"text":"So there's 2005, -6, -7, -8."},{"time":1027000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1037000,"text":"We're well on the way to achieving our initial goal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041000,"text":"We had some of the students filmed at home before they came to AIMS."},{"time":1045000,"text":"And I'll just show you one."},{"time":1048000,"text":"Tendai Mugwagwa: My name is Tendai Mugwagwa."},{"time":1052000,"text":"I have a Bachelor of Science with an education degree."},{"time":1055000,"text":"I will be attending AIMS."},{"time":1057000,"text":"My understanding of the course is that it covers quite a lot."},{"time":1061000,"text":"You know, from physics to medicine,"},{"time":1065000,"text":"in particular, epidemiology and also mathematical modeling."},{"time":1071000,"text":"Neil Turok: So Tendai came to AIMS and did very well."},{"time":1076000,"text":"And I'll let her take it from there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1084000,"text":"TM: My name is Tendai Mugwagwa"},{"time":1086000,"text":"and I was a student at AIMS in 2003 and 2004."},{"time":1090000,"text":"After leaving AIMS, I went on to do a master's in applied mathematics"},{"time":1095000,"text":"at the University of Cape Town in South Africa."},{"time":1098000,"text":"After that, I came to the Netherlands"},{"time":1100000,"text":"where I'm now doing a Ph.D. in theoretical immunology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1103000,"text":"Professor: Tendai is working very independently."},{"time":1106000,"text":"She communicates well with the immunologists at the hospital."},{"time":1110000,"text":"So all in all I have a very good Ph.D. student from South Africa."},{"time":1114000,"text":"So I'm happy she's here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1117000,"text":"NT: Another student in the first year of AIMS was Shehu."},{"time":1121000,"text":"And he's shown here with his favorite high school teacher."},{"time":1126000,"text":"And then entering university in northern Nigeria."},{"time":1132000,"text":"And after AIMS, Shehu wanted to do high-energy physics,"},{"time":1137000,"text":"and he came to Cambridge."},{"time":1139000,"text":"He's about to finish his Ph.D.,"},{"time":1142000,"text":"and he was filmed recently with someone you all know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1146000,"text":"Shehu: And from there we will be able to,"},{"time":1148000,"text":"hopefully, make better predictions and then we compare it"},{"time":1151000,"text":"to the graph and also make some predictions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1156000,"text":"Stephen Hawking: That is nice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1159000,"text":"NT: Here are the current students at AIMS. There are 53 of them"},{"time":1162000,"text":"from 20 different countries, including 20 women."},{"time":1166000,"text":"So now I'm going to get to my TED business."},{"time":1169000,"text":"Well, we had a party. This is Africa --"},{"time":1172000,"text":"we have good parties in Africa. And last month, they threw a surprise party for me."},{"time":1176000,"text":"Here's somebody you've seen already."},{"time":1178000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1202000,"text":"I want to point out a few other exceptional people in this picture."},{"time":1206000,"text":"So, we were having a party,"},{"time":1207000,"text":"as you can see they're completely eclipsing me at this point."},{"time":1211000,"text":"This is Ezra. She's from Darfur."},{"time":1214000,"text":"She's a physicist, and somehow stays smiling,"},{"time":1218000,"text":"in spite of everything going on back home."},{"time":1220000,"text":"But she wants to continue in physics, and she's doing extremely well."},{"time":1224000,"text":"This is Lydia. Lydia is the first ever woman"},{"time":1228000,"text":"to graduate in mathematics in the Central African Republic."},{"time":1231000,"text":"And she's now at AIMS. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1237000,"text":"So now let me get to our TED wish."},{"time":1241000,"text":"Well, it's not my TED wish; it's our wish, as you've already gathered."},{"time":1246000,"text":"And our wish has two parts:"},{"time":1249000,"text":"one is a dream and the other's a plan. OK."},{"time":1254000,"text":"Our TED dream is that the next Einstein will be African. (Applause)"},{"time":1273000,"text":"In striving for the heights of creative genius,"},{"time":1274000,"text":"we want to give thousands of people the motivation,"},{"time":1279000,"text":"the encouragement and the courage"},{"time":1281000,"text":"to obtain the high-level skills they need to help Africa."},{"time":1286000,"text":"Among them will be not only brilliant scientists --"},{"time":1289000,"text":"I'm sure of that from what we've seen at AIMS --"},{"time":1292000,"text":"they'll also be the African Gates, Brins and Pages of the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1298000,"text":"Well, I said we also have a plan. And our plan is quite simple."},{"time":1302000,"text":"AIMS is now a proven model."},{"time":1304000,"text":"And what we need to do is to replicate it."},{"time":1308000,"text":"We want to roll out 15 AIMS centers in the next five years, all over Africa."},{"time":1312000,"text":"Each will have a pan-African student body,"},{"time":1317000,"text":"but specialize in a different area of science."},{"time":1319000,"text":"We want to use science to overcome the national and cultural barriers,"},{"time":1324000,"text":"as it does at AIMS."},{"time":1325000,"text":"And we want to add elements to the curriculum."},{"time":1327000,"text":"We want to add entrepreneurship and policy skills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1332000,"text":"The expanded AIMS will be a coherent pan-African institution,"},{"time":1335000,"text":"and its graduates will form a powerful network,"},{"time":1339000,"text":"working together for peace and progress across the continent."},{"time":1345000,"text":"Over the last year,"},{"time":1347000,"text":"we've been visiting sites in Africa,"},{"time":1349000,"text":"looking at potential sites for new AIMS centers."},{"time":1352000,"text":"And here are the ones we've selected."},{"time":1354000,"text":"And each of these centers has a strong local team,"},{"time":1358000,"text":"each is in a beautiful place, an interesting place,"},{"time":1360000,"text":"which international lecturers will be happy to visit."},{"time":1363000,"text":"And our partners across Africa are extremely enthusiastic about this."},{"time":1368000,"text":"Everyone wants an AIMS center in their country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1372000,"text":"And last November,"},{"time":1374000,"text":"the conference of all the African ministers of science and technology,"},{"time":1378000,"text":"held in Mombasa, called for a comprehensive plan to roll out AIMS."},{"time":1383000,"text":"So we have political support right across the continent."},{"time":1386000,"text":"It won't be easy."},{"time":1389000,"text":"At every site there will be huge challenges."},{"time":1391000,"text":"Local scientists must play leading roles"},{"time":1394000,"text":"and governments must be persuaded to buy in."},{"time":1398000,"text":"Conditions are very difficult,"},{"time":1400000,"text":"but we cannot afford to compromise on those principles which made AIMS work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1407000,"text":"And we summarize them this way:"},{"time":1409000,"text":"the institutes have got to be relevant, innovative,"},{"time":1412000,"text":"cost-effective and high quality. Why?"},{"time":1414000,"text":"Because we want Africa to be rich."},{"time":1417000,"text":"Easy to remember the basic rules we need."},{"time":1424000,"text":"So, just in ending, let me say the only people who can fix Africa"},{"time":1427000,"text":"are talented young Africans."},{"time":1430000,"text":"By unlocking and nurturing their creative potential,"},{"time":1433000,"text":"we can create a step change in Africa's future."},{"time":1437000,"text":"Over time, they will contribute to African development"},{"time":1441000,"text":"and to science in ways we can only imagine."},{"time":1444000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1446000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}